,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"order to use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s methods. Do not create instances of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directly, and do not create your own subclasses of this class. The shape"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"classes correspond to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types in the GeoJSON standard, but some have nonstandard names for backwards"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compatibility."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Although you do not create instances of this class directly, you can use its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape\/shapeWithData:encoding:error:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" factory method to create one of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"concrete subclasses of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" noted above from GeoJSON data. To access a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shape’s attributes, use the corresponding "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class instead."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add shapes to the map by adding them to an "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Configure the appearance of an "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s or "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shapes collectively using a concrete instance of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorStyleLayer","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can add some kinds of shapes directly to a map view as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotations or overlays."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can filter the features in a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorStyleLayer","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or vary their layout or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"paint attributes based on the features’ geographies. Pass an "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","type":"reference"},